<item>
            <title>[LU-17138] Avoid poor performing crypto engines for client-side encryption</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17138</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Lustre client encryption relies on the llcrypt lib to carry out encryption/decryption. This lib leverages the kernel Crypto API to choose the crypto cipher to use. By default it looks for generic implementations of xts(aes), cts(cbc(aes)) and cbc(aes).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While this is fine most of the time, we might want to avoid using some cipher implementations that register under the generic name. For instance, if a cipher is provided by an external accelerator card, we might want to avoid it and prefer in-CPU engines.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="78066">LU-17138</key>
